        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 12:20PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1220 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Canon City, or 36 miles west of Pueblo, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Florence, Royal Gorge, Canon City, and Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
